President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on September 27, 2019, honoring Gold Star Mothers and Families. He expressed deep sympathy, respect, support, and gratitude towards the families who have lost loved ones in service to the country. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices made by military families, including multiple deployments, relocations, and separations. The designation of Gold Star is given to families who have experienced the life-altering loss of a family member in the line of duty. Despite their challenges and heartbreak, Gold Star families demonstrate remarkable grace and resilience, finding hope, purpose, and joy while serving as an inspiration to others. The proclamation designates Sunday, September 29, 2019, as Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day and encourages government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to honor and express gratitude for Gold Star Mothers and Families.